hr size=1> Could wizards use a buff (mele proc type) that would make them more desired in holy trinity groups?  Sure, I really like the idea of wizards being able to add temporary proc damage to weapons.<br>
<br>
Is it necessary and essential to the wizard class to achieve balance or group utility?  No.<br>
<br>
The real problem here is that there is a perception that the trinity classes are absolutely required to gain exp in EQ.  There is real basis for this argument though as SoE makes it harder and harder for casters to do anything without a PC tank (aggro changes etc.), but another aspect of this problem is the originality and creativity of the players.  <br>
<br>
There is a definite perception among most players, casters included, that you must have tanks and healers to do anything that you cannot do solo.  This simply is not the case.  There are lots of options.  Aggro kiting, tandum quadding, and all caster groups are all possibilities.  Are they as efficient as trinity groups?  probably not, but I guarentee you that they are more efficient than whining on EQ boards, waiting for SoE to change its mind, or spending hours LFG.  <br>
<br>
The only real problem is that as SoE makes more and more mobs summon they make tanks, healers, and slowers a de facto requirement and that is a true problem.  I think the solution to this problem is obvious.  SOE, STOP MAKING ALL MOBS SUMMON.  There are other way for them to fix this problem and achieve the same end.  Make exploited or unbalanced mobs more resistant (requiring more assistance from mages for malo, or enchanters for tash), add to their HPs putting them out of solo quad range, or make them unsnareable/unrootable.<br>
<br>
Next time you are LFG and sitting on your ass at the PoV zone in, look at the list of other &quot;undesireables&quot; and try to think of a strat that you can use in conjunction with them and help each other out.  This is a hell of a lot more fun than sitting on your ass and it is a great way to learn alternative ways to use your class.<br>
<br>
Some tandums/groups that work great from my experience (non summoning mobs) are: <br>
Wizard/necro<br>
wizard/rogue<br>
wizard/mage<br>
Wizard/Wizard<br>
Wizard/Druid<br>
Wizard/Ranger<br>
<br>
There are always other wizards, necros, and mages waiting around for a group.<br>
<br>
The possibilities are only limited by your imagination and your tactics.  Next time you are getting ready to complain about not getting groups try to link up with these other classes and see if you come up with a strat to accomodate your new partner/partners.  Who knows, your strat may end up being more efficient or fun than a trinity group.<br>
<br>
Vaeldayanie <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 881<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/28/03 9:20:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26268.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Problem</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> The problem with wizards, mages and necros is that they use mana for damage. Rogues and other melee don't. There is no limit on the damage a melee can do, meaning it isn't tied to a mana bar or stamina bar, as long as they are alive and all the top melee classes rogue, monk, ranger all have aggro reduction abilities or spells. Aggro is the only limitation on melee aggro and they have ways of mitigating it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
